HEADWORD: hard-hitting
<hw>hard-hitting</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>characterized by
or full of force and vigor; forceful; <as>as, a <ex>hard-hitting</ex>
expose</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> trenchant, vigorous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>aggressive; <as>as, a <ex>hard-hitting</ex>
advertising campaign</as>. Opposite of
<ant>unaggressive</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> high-pressure.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

